data.title: Pet Food Assistance — Denton Animal Support Foundation
data.meta_description: Get pet food assistance in Denton, TX from these local organizations.
data.text:
We’re Here to Help ❤️

Denton Animal Support Foundation is dedicated to keeping your furry friend at home no matter what your circumstances. Everything we do is for the pets and the community. We are so glad that you found us — we are here to help.

Denton’s Emergency Pet Food Pantry

Denton Animal Support Foundation and the City of Denton Animal Shelter have set up anEmergency Pet Food Pantry at the Linda McNatt Animal Care & Adoption Center for Denton County residents facing income insecurity. The Emergency Pet Food Pantry provides what is available based on food donations, so it may not be able to supply specific types of feeds. With that in mind, please understand that this program is not set up to supply food permanently, and is for temporary assistance only.

Location & Hours

3717 N Elm St, Denton, TX 76207

Saturday 12pm – 3pm

Interested in contributing funds or food to the Emergency Pet Food Pantry? View our Amazon Wishlist or learn more about the program.

Our Distribution Partners

DASF does not give out pet food directly. We collect it and supply it to our distribution partners. You will need to go to one of our distribution partners to get pet food. Please contact them directly to confirm eligibility requirements and hours of operation.
